{
  "text": "Since (\u03c9 + , \u03c9 \u2212 , k) \u2208 S we have k \u03b1 \u2208 C \u2212 and \u039b \u03b1 \u2282 H + , hence \u2212ik \u03b1 + \u039b \u03b1 \u2282 H + for all \u03b1 \u2208 \u03a3. It follows that I(v) is analytic at v \u2208 V . For the convergence of the integral (2.6) we use asymptotic estimates for the hyperbolic gamma function from [22, Thm. A.1] (see also [CITATION_1] ), which imply that for compacta K \u00b1 \u2282 C + , K \u2282 R there exist R, C > 0 depending only on K \u00b1 and K such that",
